## Airframe

The airframe provides the structure for the aircraft and contains all onboard systems. It consists of a 3D printed fuselage, fixed wing, tail with the full horizontal stabiliser acting as an elavator and carbon fibre wing spar through the wing.

---

## Propulsion System

The propulsion system consists of:

- Four VTOL motors for vertical take-off and landing
- One motor for forward flight
- Five electronic speed controllers (ESCs)

Each ESC independently controls one motor.

---

## Flight Control System

The Matek F405-VTOL flight controller acts as the computer of the aircraft.

It receives data from onboard sensors and pilot commands before calculating the required motor speeds.

---

## Navigation System

Navigation is provided by:

- GPS and compass module
- Airspeed sensor

These sensors allow the aircraft to estimate its position, heading and airspeed for autonomous flight.

---

## Communication System

Pilot commands are transmitted using an ELRS radio.

The RadioMaster Pocket communicates with the ELRS receiver, which sends commands to the flight controller.

---

## Power System

Power is supplied by a 4S 5000 mAh LiPo battery connected directly to the Matek F405-VTOL power distribution board.

The Matek F405-VTOL's power distribution board distributes power to each of the five ESCs while supplying a regulated power of 5V to the flight controller and electronics.

This design removes the need for an external power distribution board.
